summary_markdown: This table presents a comparative analysis of demographic data, specifically gender and age distribution, across various credit card brands. The data is structured to show the percentage of male and female cardholders for each brand, alongside the percentage distribution across distinct age groups ranging from 15-19 years to 65+ years. Brands analyzed include Barclaycard Visa, TSB Trust card, Access NatWest, Access Midlands, Barclays MasterCard, Access Lloyds, Bank of Scotland Visa, Midland Visa, TSB MasterCard, and Co-op Bank Visa. An "Average brand" row synthesizes the overall demographic profile. The structure facilitates a direct comparison of how gender and age demographics vary or align among these different credit card offerings, highlighting potential target market segments or user bases for each.
